        <div class="row"> 
                    <div class="col-sm-4 col-md-3 col-lg-2 hidden-xs media-center-search-image-wrapper">
                <div  class="ds-1col file file-image file-image-jpeg view-mode-media_search_item_image  clearfix">

  
  <img typeof="foaf:Image" class="image-style-media-search-item-image" src="https://www.gg.ca/sites/default/files/styles/media_search_item_image/public/media/galleries/2024/04_01_Nunavut_Day1/img_9133.jpg?itok=pFqXoF24" width="250" height="250" alt="Governor General Mary Simon speaks with a man in the crowd" /></div>

            </div>
            <div class="media-center-search-inner-wrapper col-xs-12 col-sm-8 col-md-9 col-lg-10">
                          <div class="row media-center-search-title">
            <div class="col-md-12">      
                                    <p class="title_prefix"><span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2024-04-01T09:00:34-04:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime"><span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2024-04-01T00:00:00-04:00">April 01, 2024</span></span></p>
                                <h2><a href="/en/activities/2024/official-visit-nunavut">Official visit to Nunavut</a></h2>            </div>
          </div>
                          <div class="row media-center-search-body hidden-xs">
            <div class="col-md-12"><p>Governor General Mary Simon and Mr. Whit Fraser completed an official visit to Nunavut where they marked the territory’s 25th anniversary. In Iqaluit and Qikiqtarjuaq, the Governor General met with territorial dignitaries, municipal leaders, Elders and youth.</p></div>
          </div>
                </div>
    </article>



